column1: # Set denotes the name of the setbeing sequenced.
# Replicate denotes replicate within a set. There are two replicates per set per condition. Replicates with the same replicate number across conditions are associated.
# Run references date of sequencing run
# Glu denotes the name of the file of that condition and replicate combination in the uninduced condition
# Gal denotes the name of the file of that condition and replicate combination in the induced condition
# Gc denotes the name of the file of that condition and replicate combination in the induced condition with GC376
# Grl denotes the name of the file of that condition and replicate combination in the induced condition with GRL-0496
# Sequence references a constant sequence in the sequenced contig used to find the region of interest
# Position references the codon position of the reference sequence in the gene
# Start/End range refer to the codons being sequenced in the set (uninclusive of the end point)
# Sites refers to specific sites that were resequenced  individually if they were repeated
